HEADWORD: Malonic
<hw>Ma*lon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a dicarboxylic acid produced
artifically as a white crystalline substance,
<chform>CH2.(CO2H)2</chform>, and so called because obtained by the
oxidation of <xex>malic</xex> acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malonyl</ent>⟦br⟧
